<section id="1002U_S001N" variety="S001N">
<name>WINDSHIELD / WINDOWGLASS</name>
<ttl id="1002U_S001N_72YMA_T00A6" variety="T00A6">
<name>WINDOW DEFOGGER SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM000000WYG00BX" category="A" type-id="8003M" name-id="WS02F-10" from="200601">
<name>REPAIR</name>
<subpara id="RM000000WYG00BX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000000WYG00BX_01_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___000059400000">
<ptxt>REPAIR WINDOW DEFOGGER WIRE</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B106758E03" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Clean the broken wire tips with a grease, wax and silicone remover.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Place the masking tape along both sides of the wire.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Thoroughly mix the repair agent (Dupont paste No. 4817 or equivalent).</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B106759" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a fine tip brush, apply a small amount of the agent to the wire.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>After a few minutes, remove the masking tape.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Do not repair the defogger wire again for at least 24 hours.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
